    <text id="A1131T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>The writer expresses the desire to come home from school.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <name type="place">Mosey Creek Academy Virginia</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sister</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your came to hand this evening and the contents were noticed very closely. I
                    suppose Green &amp; his darling will go down to Strasburg to live I wish him
                    a happy time Mollie I will most certainly comply with your request that of not
                    answering <del hand="h1">your</del> her letter, I am not anxious to answer her
                    letter if I get one from you. I must differ with you about
                    <unclear>Lollie</unclear> thinking <orig reg="anything">any thing</orig> of me I
                        am<pb n="2"/> sure she does not but we will soon see. I know you had a nice
                    time out at W.G. you could not help it for I know it is a nice place to visit, I
                    think <unclear>Pet</unclear> has abandoned the thought of writing to me or is
                    too much taken with <unclear>Dr</unclear> so <unclear>he</unclear> can't find
                    any time you would like me home saturday. I may be there and if I had money
                    enough I think I would come sooner. I am sure Ma will let us come and if she
                    does look for us on Saturday. you must write Wednesday night and get her to add
                    a note and the <orig reg="money">mony</orig> for us to come home, use your
                    influence for us once try and persuade her to let us come <orig reg="don't"
                    >dont</orig> forget to write at the time above mentioned <orig reg="whether"
                        >wether</orig> we come or not for we <orig reg="don't">dont</orig> want to
                    start on friday <orig reg="until">untill</orig> we get <del hand="h1">an</del>
                    <add hand="h1" place="inline">
                        <orig reg="definite">deffinite</orig>
                    </add> answer,</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your Brother</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <unclear>George</unclear>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
